#
# Trace retention period (in days) - DEBUGGING INFRASTRUCTURE
#
# Controls automatic execution tracing to .log/ directory.
# This is debugging infrastructure that captures execution flow (set -x output).
#
# Behavior:
#   > 0: Tracing enabled - execution flow logged to .log/YYYY-MM-DD/HHMMSS.PID_function.trace
#     0: Tracing disabled - no trace files created
#
# Trace file format:
#   Shows function call resolution, interpreter selection, and execution flow.
#   Useful for debugging dispatch issues and understanding command execution.
#
# Trace file organization:
#   .log/
#   ├── 2025-10-26/
#   │   ├── 140523.12345_wireguard_start1.log    # stderr output
#   │   └── 140523.12345_wireguard_start1.trace  # execution trace
#   └── 2025-10-25/
#       └── ...
#
# Manual override:
#   You can also set VPN_SWITCH_TRACE_FILE explicitly to override automatic path:
#   env VPN_SWITCH_TRACE_FILE=/tmp/debug.trace vpn-switch wireguard start
#
# Cleanup:
#   Trace files follow same retention policy as log files.
#   vpn-switch logs clean removes both .log and .trace files older than retention.
#
# Default: 1 day (enable debugging during initial setup when most issues occur)
#
# Debugging workflow:
#   - Enable LOG (=1) + TRACE (=1) when debugging issues
#   - LOG captures errors (stderr), TRACE captures execution context
#   - Together they provide complete debugging information
#   - Disable both (=0) for production/silent mode
#
# Customization examples:
#   VPN_SWITCH_RETENTION_DAYS_TRACE=7     # Keep 1 week
#   VPN_SWITCH_RETENTION_DAYS_TRACE=14    # Keep 2 weeks
#   VPN_SWITCH_RETENTION_DAYS_TRACE=0     # Disable tracing
#
# Performance note: Tracing adds overhead (~10-20% slower). Enable during
# debugging, disable after resolving issues.
